		<item>
		<title>Health Trends: The best apps and wearables</title>
		<link>http://www.newspages.co.za/health-trends-the-best-apps-and-wearables/</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 26 Apr 2016 07:46:47 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Khanyie]]></dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Health Tips]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Technology]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Health]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Health Care]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.newspages.co.za/?p=6963</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[<img width="68" height="68" src="http://www.newspages.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/woman-lifting-dumbbell-fitness-tracker-68x68.jpg" class="attachment-thumbnail size-thumbnail wp-post-image" alt="woman-lifting-dumbbell-fitness-tracker" style="float: left; padding: 15px 15px 15px 0px;" srcset="http://www.newspages.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/woman-lifting-dumbbell-fitness-tracker-68x68.jpg 68w, http://www.newspages.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/woman-lifting-dumbbell-fitness-tracker-200x200.jpg 200w, http://www.newspages.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/woman-lifting-dumbbell-fitness-tracker-481x480.jpg 481w, http://www.newspages.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/woman-lifting-dumbbell-fitness-tracker-16x16.jpg 16w, http://www.newspages.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/woman-lifting-dumbbell-fitness-tracker-32x32.jpg 32w, http://www.newspages.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/woman-lifting-dumbbell-fitness-tracker-28x28.jpg 28w, http://www.newspages.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/woman-lifting-dumbbell-fitness-tracker-56x56.jpg 56w, http://www.newspages.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/woman-lifting-dumbbell-fitness-tracker-64x64.jpg 64w, http://www.newspages.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/woman-lifting-dumbbell-fitness-tracker.jpg 700w" sizes="(max-width: 68px) 100vw, 68px" />You can now be cautious of your calorie intake with these calorie counter apps and gadgets
<p>Health meets technology, here are the best apps and wearables for calorie count and fitness:</p>
Best fitness trackers for calorie counting &#8211; Jawbone UP3
<p>&#160;</p>
<p></p>
<p>Jawbone&#8217;s latest wearable, the UP3 is packed full of some of the most advanced sensors in the space, which means it takes measuring your calorie burn each day.</p>
<p>UP3 tries to take out the guesswork, using data about your height, weight, activity intensity and duration from its huge range of sensors.</p>
<p>&#160;</p>
Under Armour HealthBox
<p>&#160;</p>
<p></p>
<p>The HealthBox is made up of the Under Armour Band fitness tracker, heart rate monitor chest strap and smart scales. You can step on the scales and the in formation will be combined with your food logging data.</p>
<p>&#160;</p>
Best apps for calorie counting- MyFitnessPal app
<p>&#160;</p>
<p></p>
<p>MyFitnessPal app (iOS, Android, Blackberry, Windows) is leagues ahead of the rest when it comes to calorie counting and diet management. It has your vitals and what you want to achieve &#8211; gain, lose or maintain weight .</p>
<p>MyFitnessPal estimates how many calories your body burns without additional exercise. It&#8217;s then your job to log everything you eat and drink.</p>
<p>&#160;</p>
Best for coaching: HAPIcoach
<p>&#160;</p>
<p></p>
<p>HAPIcoach app claims to get you eating better in just five days. The idea is to take photos of what you eat, logging at least 10 meals over those five days.</p>
<p>A nutrition expert will then be able to analyse your eating habits and gradually over time help you make substantial and worthwhile changes with your diet.</p>
<p>&#160;</p>
Best for fitness trackers: Lose It!
<p>&#160;</p>
<p></p>
<p>Like MyFitnessPal, it&#8217;s built around deciding how much weight you want to lose. Then you&#8217;re given a daily calorie budget to work from. It uses your phone to scan barcodes to log meals and will calculate how many calories you&#8217;ll burn from a session in the gym.</p>
<p>It also takes into consideration all the other factors that can affect a diet such as sleep and your macronutrients intake.</p>
<p>Keeping things social is a big part of how Lose It! works. You can join groups, share your favourite meals and enter challenges to keep you motivated.</p>
]]></description>
				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<img width="68" height="68" src="http://www.newspages.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/woman-lifting-dumbbell-fitness-tracker-68x68.jpg" class="attachment-thumbnail size-thumbnail wp-post-image" alt="woman-lifting-dumbbell-fitness-tracker" style="float: left; padding: 15px 15px 15px 0px;" srcset="http://www.newspages.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/woman-lifting-dumbbell-fitness-tracker-68x68.jpg 68w, http://www.newspages.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/woman-lifting-dumbbell-fitness-tracker-200x200.jpg 200w, http://www.newspages.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/woman-lifting-dumbbell-fitness-tracker-481x480.jpg 481w, http://www.newspages.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/woman-lifting-dumbbell-fitness-tracker-16x16.jpg 16w, http://www.newspages.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/woman-lifting-dumbbell-fitness-tracker-32x32.jpg 32w, http://www.newspages.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/woman-lifting-dumbbell-fitness-tracker-28x28.jpg 28w, http://www.newspages.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/woman-lifting-dumbbell-fitness-tracker-56x56.jpg 56w, http://www.newspages.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/woman-lifting-dumbbell-fitness-tracker-64x64.jpg 64w, http://www.newspages.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/woman-lifting-dumbbell-fitness-tracker.jpg 700w" sizes="(max-width: 68px) 100vw, 68px" /><h2>You can now be cautious of your calorie intake with these calorie counter apps and gadgets</h2>
<p><strong>Health meets technology, here are the best apps and wearables for calorie count and fitness:</strong></p>
<h2 style="text-align: center"><strong>Best fitness trackers for calorie counting &#8211; Jawbone UP3</strong></h2>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><img class="size-medium wp-image-6964 aligncenter" src="http://www.newspages.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/jawbone-up3-food-tracking-1439912156-6Hoe-column-width-inline-300x169.jpg" alt="jawbone-up3-food-tracking-1439912156-6Hoe-column-width-inline" width="300" height="169" srcset="http://www.newspages.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/jawbone-up3-food-tracking-1439912156-6Hoe-column-width-inline-300x169.jpg 300w, http://www.newspages.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/jawbone-up3-food-tracking-1439912156-6Hoe-column-width-inline-768x432.jpg 768w, http://www.newspages.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/jawbone-up3-food-tracking-1439912156-6Hoe-column-width-inline-640x360.jpg 640w, http://www.newspages.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/jawbone-up3-food-tracking-1439912156-6Hoe-column-width-inline-16x9.jpg 16w, http://www.newspages.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/jawbone-up3-food-tracking-1439912156-6Hoe-column-width-inline-32x18.jpg 32w, http://www.newspages.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/jawbone-up3-food-tracking-1439912156-6Hoe-column-width-inline-28x16.jpg 28w, http://www.newspages.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/jawbone-up3-food-tracking-1439912156-6Hoe-column-width-inline-56x32.jpg 56w, http://www.newspages.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/jawbone-up3-food-tracking-1439912156-6Hoe-column-width-inline-64x36.jpg 64w, http://www.newspages.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/jawbone-up3-food-tracking-1439912156-6Hoe-column-width-inline-712x400.jpg 712w, http://www.newspages.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/jawbone-up3-food-tracking-1439912156-6Hoe-column-width-inline.jpg 865w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /></p>
<p>Jawbone&#8217;s latest wearable, the UP3 is packed full of some of the most advanced sensors in the space, which means it takes measuring your calorie burn each day.</p>
<p>UP3 tries to take out the guesswork, using data about your height, weight, activity intensity and duration from its huge range of sensors.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h2 style="text-align: center"><strong>Under Armour HealthBox</strong></h2>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><img class="size-medium wp-image-6965 aligncenter" src="http://www.newspages.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Under-Armour-HealthBox-300x168.jpg" alt="Under Armour HealthBox" width="300" height="168" srcset="http://www.newspages.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Under-Armour-HealthBox-300x168.jpg 300w, http://www.newspages.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Under-Armour-HealthBox-768x430.jpg 768w, http://www.newspages.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Under-Armour-HealthBox-640x358.jpg 640w, http://www.newspages.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Under-Armour-HealthBox-16x9.jpg 16w, http://www.newspages.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Under-Armour-HealthBox-32x18.jpg 32w, http://www.newspages.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Under-Armour-HealthBox-28x16.jpg 28w, http://www.newspages.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Under-Armour-HealthBox-56x31.jpg 56w, http://www.newspages.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Under-Armour-HealthBox-64x36.jpg 64w, http://www.newspages.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Under-Armour-HealthBox-712x400.jpg 712w, http://www.newspages.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Under-Armour-HealthBox.jpg 865w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /></p>
<p>The HealthBox is made up of the Under Armour Band fitness tracker, heart rate monitor chest strap and smart scales. You can step on the scales and the in formation will be combined with your food logging data.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h2 style="text-align: center"><strong>Best apps for calorie counting- MyFitnessPal app</strong></h2>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><img class="size-medium wp-image-6966 aligncenter" src="http://www.newspages.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/myfitnesspal-20-1460372547-fHtq-column-width-inline-300x169.jpg" alt="myfitnesspal-20-1460372547-fHtq-column-width-inline" width="300" height="169" srcset="http://www.newspages.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/myfitnesspal-20-1460372547-fHtq-column-width-inline-300x169.jpg 300w, http://www.newspages.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/myfitnesspal-20-1460372547-fHtq-column-width-inline-768x432.jpg 768w, http://www.newspages.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/myfitnesspal-20-1460372547-fHtq-column-width-inline-640x360.jpg 640w, http://www.newspages.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/myfitnesspal-20-1460372547-fHtq-column-width-inline-16x9.jpg 16w, http://www.newspages.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/myfitnesspal-20-1460372547-fHtq-column-width-inline-32x18.jpg 32w, http://www.newspages.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/myfitnesspal-20-1460372547-fHtq-column-width-inline-28x16.jpg 28w, http://www.newspages.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/myfitnesspal-20-1460372547-fHtq-column-width-inline-56x32.jpg 56w, http://www.newspages.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/myfitnesspal-20-1460372547-fHtq-column-width-inline-64x36.jpg 64w, http://www.newspages.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/myfitnesspal-20-1460372547-fHtq-column-width-inline-712x400.jpg 712w, http://www.newspages.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/myfitnesspal-20-1460372547-fHtq-column-width-inline.jpg 865w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /></p>
<p>MyFitnessPal app (iOS, Android, Blackberry, Windows) is leagues ahead of the rest when it comes to calorie counting and diet management. It has your vitals and what you want to achieve &#8211; gain, lose or maintain weight .</p>
<p>MyFitnessPal estimates how many calories your body burns without additional exercise. It&#8217;s then your job to log everything you eat and drink.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h2 style="text-align: center"><strong>Best for coaching: HAPIcoach</strong></h2>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><img class="size-medium wp-image-6967 aligncenter" src="http://www.newspages.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/hapicoach-2-1460375513-BQzS-column-width-inline-300x168.jpg" alt="hapicoach-2-1460375513-BQzS-column-width-inline" width="300" height="168" srcset="http://www.newspages.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/hapicoach-2-1460375513-BQzS-column-width-inline-300x168.jpg 300w, http://www.newspages.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/hapicoach-2-1460375513-BQzS-column-width-inline-768x431.jpg 768w, http://www.newspages.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/hapicoach-2-1460375513-BQzS-column-width-inline-640x359.jpg 640w, http://www.newspages.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/hapicoach-2-1460375513-BQzS-column-width-inline-16x9.jpg 16w, http://www.newspages.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/hapicoach-2-1460375513-BQzS-column-width-inline-32x18.jpg 32w, http://www.newspages.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/hapicoach-2-1460375513-BQzS-column-width-inline-28x16.jpg 28w, http://www.newspages.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/hapicoach-2-1460375513-BQzS-column-width-inline-56x31.jpg 56w, http://www.newspages.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/hapicoach-2-1460375513-BQzS-column-width-inline-64x36.jpg 64w, http://www.newspages.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/hapicoach-2-1460375513-BQzS-column-width-inline-712x400.jpg 712w, http://www.newspages.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/hapicoach-2-1460375513-BQzS-column-width-inline.jpg 800w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /></p>
<p>HAPIcoach app claims to get you eating better in just five days. The idea is to take photos of what you eat, logging at least 10 meals over those five days.</p>
<p>A nutrition expert will then be able to analyse your eating habits and gradually over time help you make substantial and worthwhile changes with your diet.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h2 style="text-align: center"><strong>Best for fitness trackers: Lose It!</strong></h2>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><img class="size-medium wp-image-6969 aligncenter" src="http://www.newspages.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/lose-it-300x169.jpg" alt="lose it" width="300" height="169" srcset="http://www.newspages.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/lose-it-300x169.jpg 300w, http://www.newspages.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/lose-it-768x432.jpg 768w, http://www.newspages.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/lose-it-640x360.jpg 640w, http://www.newspages.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/lose-it-16x9.jpg 16w, http://www.newspages.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/lose-it-32x18.jpg 32w, http://www.newspages.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/lose-it-28x16.jpg 28w, http://www.newspages.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/lose-it-56x32.jpg 56w, http://www.newspages.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/lose-it-64x36.jpg 64w, http://www.newspages.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/lose-it-712x400.jpg 712w, http://www.newspages.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/lose-it.jpg 800w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /></p>
<p>Like MyFitnessPal, it&#8217;s built around deciding how much weight you want to lose. Then you&#8217;re given a daily calorie budget to work from. It uses your phone to scan barcodes to log meals and will calculate how many calories you&#8217;ll burn from a session in the gym.</p>
<p>It also takes into consideration all the other factors that can affect a diet such as sleep and your macronutrients intake.</p>
<p>Keeping things social is a big part of how Lose It! works. You can join groups, share your favourite meals and enter challenges to keep you motivated.</p>
